{"questionId":"9069953","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Many reactions are in a state of equilibrium.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The pH of 0.010 mol dm<sup>–3</sup> carbonic acid, H<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>3</sub> (aq), is 4.17 at 25 °C.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">H<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>3</sub> (aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O (l) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> HCO<sub>3</sub><sup>–</sup> (aq) + H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup> (aq).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate [H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup>] in the solution and the dissociation constant, <em>K</em><sub>a</sub> , of the acid at&nbsp;25 °C.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>[H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup>]&nbsp;= 6.76&nbsp;x 10<sup>–5</sup> «mol dm<sup>–3</sup>»</p>\n<p><em>K</em><sub>a</sub> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{{\\left( {6.76 \\times {{10}^{ - 5}}} \\right)}^2}}}{{\\left( {0.010 - 6.76 \\times {{10}^{ - 5}}} \\right)}}/\\frac{{{{\\left( {6.76 \\times {{10}^{ - 5}}} \\right)}^2}}}{{0.010}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>6.76</mn>\n                <mo>×</mo>\n                <mrow>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <mn>10</mn>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <mo>−</mo>\n                      <mn>5</mn>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>0.010</mn>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>6.76